    "sw-hyperspace85-disasm": "hyperspace85  .  jmg 62\n\n/ NOTE: the original source has been discovered since this disassembly was made.\n/ Please refer to http://www.masswerk.at/sources/hyperspace85.txt\n\n/ disassembly of the patch \"hyperspace85.bin\"\n/ http://bitsavers.org/bits/DEC/pdp1/papertapeImages/20031202/InsidePDP1_80s_box3/hyperspace85.bin\n/\n/ (disassembly by N. Landsteiner, June 2014, www.masswerk.at)\n/ any addresses smaller than 5240 (start of patch) are referring to spacewar 2b\n/ (the symbols and locations of variables are matching perfectly)\n/ all symbols used inside the patch are generic and without meaning\n/ (jumps to return addresses are using labels ending in \"x\").\n/ productions of the macro assembler are prefixed by \"*\".\n\n/ symbols of spacewar 2b used by the patch\nml1=1540\nmb1=1637\nmx1=1567\nmy1=1577\nmco=2254\nmh1=2665\t\t/ \\mh1 (variable)\nmh2=2666\t\t/ \\mh2 (variable)\nmh3=2667\t\t/ \\mh3 (variable)\nscw=2673\t\t/ \\scw (variable)\nsr5=2341\nran=2654\t\t/ \\ran (variable)\nnb1=3243\n\n/ macros used\n\n\tdefine initialize A,B\n\tlaw B\n\tdap A\n\tterm\n\n\tdefine index A,B,C\n\tidx A\n\tsas B\n\tjmp C\n\tterm\n\n\tdefine swap\n\trcl 9s\n\trcl 9s\n\tterm\n\n\tdefine setup A,B\n\tlaw i B\n\tdac A\n\tterm\n\n\tdefine count A,B\n\tisp A\n\tjmp B\n\tterm\n\n/ macro random using constants like spacewar 2b, but local to the patch\n\n\tdefine hrandom\n\tlac ran\t\t/\\ran\n\trar 1s\n\txor hc6\t\t/(335671\n\tadd hc6\t\t/(335671\n\tdac ran\t\t/\\ran\n\tterm\n\n\n/ patched locations\n\n1456/                                                   / a1-1\n01456     605530     jmp 5530        jmp hq4\n\n1525/                                                   / mg1-2\n01525     175507     jda 5507        jda hq5\n\n1642/                                                   / mq1\n01642     625570     jsp 5570        jsp hti\n\n2341/                                                   / sr5\n02341     605545     jmp 5545        jmp hq3\n\n\n\n/ star